OL,6,FAs it's made, each tonne of ACLA takes
OL,7,F750 kg of CO2 from the atmosphere.
OL,8,FMixing even just 5% of it with normal
OL,9,Fasphalt, will significantly lower the
OL,10,Fcarbon footprint, enabling net zero
OL,11,Froads.
OL,13,FDr Natasha Boulding is Chief Executive
OL,14,Fof Low Carbon Materials, the Seaham
OL,15,Fbased company behind the new material:
OL,16,F"I think people take the built
OL,17,Fenvironment for-granted sometimes,
OL,18,Fwhether it's our houses, our offices,
OL,19,For even our roads"
